-U[prints to screen url output map of available output possibilities]
-u[url mapping of output files for requested processing flags]
-V[more verbose than -v]
-v[verbose]
-A[plaintext with dos line-feeds, footnotes follow paragraphs in which they occur]
-a[plaintext with Unix line-feeds, footnotes follow paragraphs in which they occur]
-b[XHTML output]
-C[initialise site]
-c[toggle screen color on or off depending on set default]
-E[plaintext with dos line-feeds, endnotes following main text]
-e[plaintext with Unix line-feeds, endnotes following main text]
-F[generate sample cgi web search form \[--webserv=webrick for sisu webrick url\]
-H[HTML output, without link suffixes]
-h[HTML output]
-I[texinfo output, not maintained]
-L[print license info]
-M[maintenance mode, retain intermediate processing files]
-m[create intermediate markup file, metaverse, assumed for most output instuctions]
-N[document content certificate, output document digests]
-n[skip intermediate markup, skip -m]
-o[Open Document text format output]
-p[LaTeX pdf output]
-q[quiet mode]
-R[post output to remote host using rsync, requires pre-configuration]
-r[post output to remote host using scp, requires pre-configuration]
-S[produces and shares tarred gzipped markup source document with associated images etc.]
-s[shares markup source]
-t[termsheet, preprocessing]
-W[starts ruby webrick server]
-w[concordance file]
-X[XML dom style]
-x[XML sax style]
-y[output summary page, manifest of existing generated output]
-Z[zap delete/destroy output]
